   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>Subject One Hundred Seventy-eight CHRIST JESUS CAME INTO THE WORLD</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>TO SAVE SINNERS Scripture: 1 Tim 1:15 Who is Christ Jesus?</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>Christ signifies that He is God.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>Jesus signifies that He is man.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>The compound name of Christ Jesus means that God came as man to save men and to become the Savior of mankind.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>Why did Christ Jesus come into the world?</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>Christ Jesus did not come into the world by accident or without a purpose.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>Christ Jesus came into the world in order to save sinners.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>Who are the sinners?</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>All men are sinners.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>As long as you are a man in this world, you are a sinner.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>Christ Jesus came into this world in order to save sinners, that is, to save you.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>As far as I am concerned, He came to save me; as far as you are concerned, He came to save you.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>How can man receive the salvation of Christ Jesus?</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>Develop this point.</S>
   </TEXT>
